hopobject.body: What sort of work do you do? pharmacy mgm grand Last summer's discovery of the so-called "God particle" has been at the center of a multi-billion dollar effort at the CERN research center in Switzerland to understand why objects in the universe harbor mass. The Higgs boson, a subatomic particle, has long been held as a missing puzzle piece in the Standard Model of Physics. It is the invisible glue that keeps the atoms comprising our universe's planets, stars, and human beings clumped together. Without it, the theory goes, our atoms would be zipping around all over the place.
